OL,4,Cbodies in un-cooled mortuary, court
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMs Bates said Mr Mitchell's family
OL,8,F"were incredulous" when told by police
OL,9,Fthat his body had not been cremated in
OL,10,Fthe planned private cremation, and had
OL,11,Feven placed a wreath at Portchester
OL,12,FCrematorium in the "mistaken belief
OL,13,Fthat his body had been cremated there".
OL,15,FShe said: "In any properly managed
OL,16,Ffirm of undertakers, there was no good
OL,17,Freason, it is submitted, why the
OL,18,Fcremation of the body of William
OL,19,FMitchell should have been subject to
OL,20,Fany undue delay."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/14
