OL,3,CFuneral directors left decomposing
OL,4,Cbodies in un-cooled mortuary, court
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMs Bates said that Mr Elkin told
OL,8,Fpolice he had not been involved in the
OL,9,Fbusiness for two years and it had been
OL,10,Fthe responsibility of Ms Bell, but the
OL,11,Fprosecutor said that he had been
OL,12,F"actively involved", including
OL,13,Fcollecting the body of Mr Mitchell
OL,14,Ffrom his home.
OL,16,FThey said they had been aware of a
OL,17,Fproblem with the roof and were waiting
OL,18,Ffor the landlord to carry out repairs,
OL,19,Fand Mr Elkin said that the
OL,20,Frefrigeration unit must have broken,
OL,21,Fthe court heard.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/14
